<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-04T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-04T10:00:00-05:00" n="550" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d550">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/10–446: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to
                                the British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Attlee</hi></persName>)<note n="74" xml:id="d550fn74">Sent to London as Department’s telegram 6988, with
                                the instruction: “Please deliver the following message to the Prime
                                Minister urgently from the President.”</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-04T10:00:00-05:00">October 4,
                                    1946—10 a.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Prime Minister</hi>: I am very sorry
                            indeed that I cannot comply with the request you made of me in your
                            message yesterday<note n="75" xml:id="d550fn75">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> to postpone making the
                            statement on Palestine. For reasons which have been fully explained to
                            the Ambassador here and by Mr. Byrnes to Mr. Bevin, it is imperative
                            that I make my position clear today.<note n="76" xml:id="d550fn76">The
                                President’s statement was released by the White House on October
                                4.</note>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>